    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "About the role:\n\nThis opportunity gives you the chance to develop, maintain, and distribute our mobile apps, which are our core product, interacting with a deep tech problem directly in the application. We are looking for long-term players, professionals who are looking to grow and evolve with us over time. Additionally, individuals who have worked at product-focused companies tend to stand out, since they usually bring a deep understanding of building and scaling solutions with the end user in mind. Lastly, experience in start-up environments is highly regarded, as it often reflects adaptability, initiative, and the ability to thrive in dynamic, fast-paced settings.\n\nWhat you’ll do:\n\n - Collaborate with product, design, and other engineers for new features.\n\n - Design and implement key functionality in the apps.\n\n - Develop tooling to improve our development practices.\n\n - Participate in code reviews to raise the quality of our code and our product.\n\n - Own your code in production.\n\n - Work with our CX team when users are having trouble with the app.\n\nWhat you’ll bring or Qualifications:\n\n - Expertise in mobile SDKs and application development, including common design patterns.\n\n - Our team possesses cross-team collaboration skills, and we are highly cross-functional, bringing everyone to the table to address our problems.\n\n - A beginner’s mindset, always striving to understand.\n\n - Own and solve problems.\n\n - Willing and able to work on open problems.\n\n - Being open to solving whatever needs to be solved.\n\nOur Tech Stack\n\n - iOS: Swift, UIKit, RxSwift, Golang.\n\n - Android: Kotlin, RxJava, Golang\n\nInterview Process\n\n - Silver Screening Interview.\n\n - Silver Technical Interview.\n\n - Client Screening Interview.\n\n - TakeHome Challenge.\n\n - DeepDive Interview\n\n - Behavioral Interview.",
